---
layout: layouts/base.njk
css: tickets.css
---

<style>
  h2 {
    font-size: 28px;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.28;
    letter-spacing: normal;
    color: var(--primary);
    margin-top: 28px;
  }

  .tickets {
    padding: 0 32px;
  }

  @media only screen and (min-width: 700px) {
    .tickets .grid {
      position: relative;
      display: flex;
      gap: 32px;
    }


    .tickets .grid main {
      order: -1;
      flex: 1;
    }

    .tickets aside {
      height: 100vh;
      position: sticky;
      top: 0;
      width: 340px;
    }
  }

  .tickets .ticket-buy {
    a {
      background: black;
      padding: 20px 40px;
      color: white;
      font-size: 110%;
      border-radius: 100px;
      text-decoration: none;
      flex: 1;
      text-align: center;

      &:hover {
        text-decoration: underline;
        text-decoration-thickness: 2px;
        background: white;
        color: black;
        outline: 4px solid black;
      }
    }

    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .tickets blockquote strong {
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .tickets blockquote+blockquote {
    margin-top: 4em;
  }

  .tickets ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    margin-top: 48px;
    padding: 0;

    li {
      margin: 16px 0;
    }
  }

  .tickets .summary {
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  rem-days-to {
    slot {
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    font-weight: bold;
    text-align: center;
    display: block;
  }
</style>

<section class="tickets">
  <header>
    <h1>FFConf {% year %} tickets</h1>
  </header>

  <div class="grid">
    <aside>
      <when-do datetime="2026-06-25T10:00:00" do="show">
        <p><rem-days-to date="{{ tickets.date  | format("YYYY-MM-DD") }}"><slot>Not many</slot> working days left to get your&nbsp;ticket!</rem-days-to></p>
        <p class="ticket-buy"><a href="{{ tickets.url }}">Buy tickets now</a></p>
      </when-do>
      <when-do datetime="2026-06-25T10:00:00" do="hide">
        <p><rem-days-to date="{{ tickets.launch  | format("YYYY-MM-DD") }}">Tickets available in <slot>a short number of</slot> days!</rem-days-to></p>
        <p class="ticket-buy"><a href="{{ next.url }}">Tickets on sale soon</a></p>
      </when-do>

      <p>{{ tickets.date | format }} - 9am-6pm</p>
      <p class="summary">Eight sessions on {{ tickets.summary }}</p>
      <script src="/assets/rem-days-to.wc.mjs"></script>
      <script src="/assets/when-do.wc.mjs"></script>

      <ul>
        <li>🗓️ {{tickets.date | format }} in Brighton</li>
        <li>⏰ 9-6pm all day conference</li>
        <li>🌟 8 amazing and inspiring talks</li>
        <li>😌 Incredibly comfortable seats</li>
        <li>🏰 Held at <a target="_blank"
            href="https://www.picturehouses.com/cinema/duke-of-york-s-picturehouse/information">Duke of
            Yorks</a> cinema</li>
        <li>🤗 After party to socialise, network or play board games</li>
        <li>🦾 Inclusion scholarship programme</li>
        <li>🌈 Sunshine 100% (not) guaranteed</li>
        <li>🎟️ <a target="_blank" href="https://{{ collections.currentYear.year }}.ffconf.org">Learn more about the
            sessions</a></li>
      </ul>

    </aside>
    <main>
      <h2>About FFConf</h2>

      <p>FFConf is a room full of people who still give a damn about the web and it's community - talks meant to be experienced, <em>not</em> bookmarked.</p>

      <h2>Who should attend?</h2>
      <p>Anyone who works on or with the web and hasn't stopped caring about it. ffconf isn't for a job title, it's for a disposition - developers, designers, the people who manage them and the people who brief them. If you're only half-sure you still care, a day in this room tends to fix that.</p>

      <h2>Why attend?</h2>

      <p>People don't leave ffconf with a tidy list of takeaways. They leave with the itch to try something - a new job, a first blog post, their own name on a CFP. The talks start it; the room makes it stick. You had to be there, and that's not a slogan - it's the mechanism.</p>

      <h2 id="august">A note on August</h2>

      <p>We close our ticket sales during the month of August. This allows you and us to have a little break during the holidays, though our early bird tickets, if available, also end during this period too.</p>

